# This installs fcitx on GNOME (Orance-Gray, use Compose Key, Ubuntu Unity native Chinese input)
## ** This uses an unknown dependency (probably from Canonical) not native to GNOME. Installing Ubuntu Studio seems to provide it.
## ** Without this dependency, the qimpanel selector skins can't render either in settings preview or typing.

## Also: The Canonical skin (orange, gray, etc) is overridden by the Fcitx skin settings
## ** Solution: Run fcitx-qimpanel-configtool BEFORE running Fcitx or Fcitx Configuration!! (Otherwise, reinstall OS to fix, haha.)

# Prerequesites for this to work
## 1. Ubuntu Studio installed via command line (see vStudio and vGNOME-all - can be done after these instructions)
## 2. Run fcitx-qimpanel-configtool right away, after installing fcitx (below - can't be undone if skipped)

#Instructions:

sudo apt-get install fcitx fcitx-ui-qimpanel fcitx-chewing fcitx-table-cangjie
## Run fcitx-qimpanel-configtool from the GNOME dashboard menu, then exit (creating configs)
im-config
## Yes, yes, fcitx, yes
cat ~/.xinputrc
echo 'run_im fcitx' > ~/.xinputrc
## sudo reboot
ps aux | grep ibus
ps aux | grep fcitx
sudo apt-get purge ibus
## sudo reboot

## If gcin is installed
ps aux | grep gcin
sudo apt-get purge gcin
## sudo reboot


